n%20of%20poverty.%20You%20see%2C%20someone%20who%20is%20used%20to%20wearing%20fine%20shoes%20will%20feel%20their%20absence%20when%20they%20don't%20have%20them.%20But%20for%20us%2C%20we%20had%20never%20worn%20shoes%20in%20our%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Modi%20told%20podcast%20host%20Lex%20Fridman%2C%20adding%20these%20%26quot%3Bchallenging%20circumstances%20of%20living%20in%20scarcity%20never%20left%20a%20mark%20on%20our%20minds%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20who%20won%20a%20record%20third%20term%20last%20year%2C%20recounted%20how%20he%20once%20ran%20into%20his%20uncle%20who%20was%20surprised%20to%20see%20him%20going%20to%20school%20without%20shoes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20I%20was%20on%20my%20way%20to%20school%2C%20I%20ran%20into%20my%20uncle%20on%20the%20way.%20He%20saw%20me%20and%20was%20surprised%2C%20'Hey!%20You%20go%20to%20school%20like%20this%3F%20Without%20shoes%3F'%20So%20at%20that%20time%2C%20he%20bought%20me%20a%20pair%20of%20canvas%20shoes%20and%20made%20me%20wear%20them.%20Back%20then%2C%20they%20must%20have%20cost%20around%2010%20or%2012%20rupees.%20But%20here's%20the%20thing%2C%20they%20were%20white%20canvas%20shoes%2C%20and%20they%20would%20quickly%20get%20stained%2C%26quot%3B%20reflected%20PM%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20received%20the%20shoes%2C%20the%20next%20worry%20that%20gripped%20him%20was%20how%20to%20keep%20them%20clean.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20evening%2C%20after%20school%20was%20over%2C%20I%20would%20stay%20back%20for%20a%20while.%20I%20would%20go%20from%20classroom%20to%20classroom%2C%20collecting%20leftover%20pieces%20of%20chalk%20that%20the%20teachers%20had%20discarded.%20I%20would%20take%20the%20pieces%20of%20chalk%20home%2C%20soak%20them%20in%20water%2C%20mix%20them%20into%20a%20paste%2C%20and%20polish%20my%20canvas%20shoes%20with%20it%2C%20making%20them%20bright%20white%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20detailing%20his%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20those%20shoes%20were%20a%20treasured%20possession%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20great%20wealth.%20And%20I%20don't%20exactly%20know%20why%2C%20but%20from%20childhood%2C%20our%20mother%20was%20extremely%20particular%20about%20cleanliness.%20Perhaps%20that's%20where%20we%20inherited%20that%20habit%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20detailed%20how%20managed%20to%20keep%20his%20clothes%20ironed%20despite%20having%20no%20such%20arrangements.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20sure%20how%20I%20picked%20up%20the%20habit%20of%20dressing%20neatly%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20there%20since%20childhood.%20Whatever%20I%20wore%2C%20I%20made%20sure%20it%20looked%20proper.%20Back%20then%2C%20as%20you%20can%20imagine%2C%20we%20didn't%20have%20any%20arrangements%20for%20ironing%20clothes.%20So%20instead%2C%20I%20would%20heat%20up%20water%20in%20a%20copper%20pot%2C%20hold%20it%20with%20tongs%2C%20and%20press%20my%20clothes%20myself.%20Then%2C%20I'd%20head%20off%20to%20school.%20That's%20how%20I%20lived%2C%20and%20I%20found%20joy%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM%20Modi%20emphasised%20that%20he%20embraced%20every%20phase%20of%20life%20with%20gratitude%20and%20never%20viewed%20poverty%20as%20a%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20never%20thought%20about%20being%20poor%2C%20or%20judged%20about%20how%20others%20lived%2C%20or%20what%20their%20struggles%20were.%20We%20lived%20carefree%2C%20enjoying%20whatever%20little%20we%20had%2C%20and%20kept%20working%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742132280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fnglg2nqo_pm-modi-_625x300_16_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-lex-fridman-podcast-white-shoes-and-the-problem-of-keeping-them-clean-how-pm-modi-solved-it-as-a-child-7936906%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22